Equity Research August 28, 2025

SF Intra- city announced preliminary earnings on 20 Aug and reported results today. During conference call, mgt highlighted solid order volume seen QTD and expects 3Q volume to accelerate YoY vs 1H, thanks to the deepening in co- operation with key accounts, intra- city delivery for consumers and synergies with its parent company. On full year basis, we revise up total revenue factoring the recent trends and estimate non- IFRS earnings to double YoY. Maintain Buy.

1H25 results highlights. SF Intra- city released preliminary profit alert on 20 Aug and reported results today. Total revenue increased \(48.8\%\) YoY (vs guidance no less than \(45\%\) YoY) to RMB10.2bn, \(5.7\%\) above our estimates. For intra- city on demand delivery service, revenue grew \(43.1\%\) YoY to RMB5.8bn (inline with our estimates). Revenue from last- mile delivery service rose \(56.9\%\) to RMB4.5bn (vs our estimate of RMB3.9bn). Gross profit improved by \(43.8\%\) YoY to RMB680.8m with GPM reaching \(6.7\%\) (vs our estimate of \(6.9\%\) ). Operating profit reached RMB150.1m compared with RMB62.6m in 1H24 and our estimate at RMB124.8m. Net profit attributable to owners of company increased by \(120\%\) YoY (vs guidance of no less than \(100\%\) YoY growth) to RMB137m (vs our estimates at RMB125m). Non- IFRS net profit reached RMB160.2m with net profit margin at \(1.6\%\) (vs our estimate of RMB136m and \(1.4\%\) net margin).

Key takeaways from conference call. These include: (1) Industry trend. (a) Management views the on- demand delivery industry has a cycle of more than five years as food delivery and on- demand retail satisfy the young generation's consumption needs; (b) there will be more and more players in the industry; (c) brand concentration and customer concentration will continue to increase. (2) 3Q momentum. Co expects its revenue growth in 3Q25 will be faster than 1H25. (a) At 0 B end, leveraging its high- quality services, it has deepened cooperation with KA customers; (b) at 0 C end, revenue growth is driven by both industry momentum and its high- quality one- on- one "Exclusive Delivery" services; (c) for last- mile delivery services, it has deepened network and business collaboration with SF Holding and gained more share. (3) Merchants. As of Jun 2025, the number of active merchants in the past 12 months on its platform reached 850K, representing a YoY increase of \(55\%\) . In 1H25, revenue from tea beverage delivery increased by \(105\%\) YoY, while categories such as supermarket and convenience stores, pharmaceuticals, and maternal and baby products all achieved high double- digit growth. (4) Consumers. As of Jun 2025, the number of active consumers in the past 12 months reached 24.77m, with increased order frequency and strong repurchases from existing customers. (5) Riders. SF Intra- city is the largest independent third- party on- demand delivery platform in China, providing multiple platforms with high- quality, efficient, and reliable services. It has comprehensive riders, resources which include two and four wheels riders for different delivery services. It has strong technological capability to achieve higher efficiencies, while lowering delivery cost through a superior City Logistics System (CLS) with big data and AI technologies. The mutually beneficial partnership with SF Holding Group allows SF Intra- city to provide more comprehensive services to customers, which helps to broaden its customer reach and increase customer retention.
Risk/Reward - 12 Month View

We estimate total revenue to grow \(32\%\) YoY in 2025, thanks to rapid growth in nonfood delivery, intra- city delivery to consumers, and increasing penetration in lower- tier cities. We estimate overall GPM to remain stable YoY considering the time needed to achieve leverage due to surge in demand. We believe that the company continues to generate Non- IFRS net profit in 2025, thanks to economies of scale, efficiencies of delivery networks, refined operations and management, as well as differentiated services driving high- value orders. PT of HKD23 based on P/S valuation.

Top Material Issue(s): In- Customer Privacy. The use and storage of a wide range of customer data, such as personal demographic, content, and behavioral data, raise privacy concerns, leading to increased regulatory scrutiny. 2) Employee Health & Safety. Company needs to provide adequate protection and training for employees, ensure mechanical equipment is safely functioning, and establish a culture of safety within the workplace.

Company Target(s): 1) SF Intra- city commits to reducing office electricity intensity in 2025 vs 2024. 2) It strives to lower office water intensity in 2025 vs 2024. 3) It also targets to reduce office waste intensity in 2025 vs 2024.
Qs to Mgmt: 1) What are you investing in to protect your firm's and your customers' data? 2) What measures are you taking to protect the health and safety of your employees?

Slower- than- expected revenue growth in intra- city delivery service. Slower- than- expected revenue growth in last- mile delivery service. Softer- than- expected margin due to aggressive investment. PT of HKD11 based on P/S valuation.
Stronger- than- expected customer growth. Higher- than- expected order volume and order density. Expanding into new scenarios. Higher- than- expected operating efficiency.

productivity improved by \(38\%\) YoY, leading to continued improvement in riders' income. The number of riders with medium- to- high income levels increased by \(65\%\) YoY and the number of riders with an average monthly income exceeding RM1oK increased by \(107\%\) YoY. Benefited from its direct operating model, the company has better understanding of its riders. In addition, it has a good promotion mechanism for riders, which has attracted over 200K younger riders aged between 18 and 22. (6) GPM. In 1H25, GPM slightly narrowed by 0.2pp YoY mainly due to an increasing spending on riders in May to ensure service quality and fulfillment amid the intensified competition in food delivery industry. This spending has gradually stabilized and declined after May and Co expects a stable GPM going forward. (7) OPEX as a \(\%\) of revenue decreased from \(6.2\%\) in 1H24 to \(5.4\%\) in 1H25. Management targets to lower it to \(4\%\) in the next one to two years. It will continue to spend on R&D and G&A to attract excellent talents while improve marketing efficiency through digitalized tools. (8) Unmanned vehicles. As of Jun 2025, over 300 unmanned vehicles had been put into daily operation, covering more than 60 cities nationwide, with an average of approximately 20K active trips per month. Co expects to put into operation thousands of unmanned vehicles by 2028 which will help improve cost efficiency. The unmanned vehicles will deliver parcels for its parent SF Holding, as well as other players. (9) Al. In 1H25, Co actively promoted multi- scenario applications of Al large models, cooperating with a number of leading domestic large model vendors, and applying self- developed Al agent tools in areas such as rider management, local delivery outlet manager services, intelligent customer service, and merchant operations to assist in communication, information collection, operational analysis, and anomaly monitoring. The application of Al has effectively driven upgrades in experience and efficiency across the entire process.

Valuation and risks. We maintain Buy and adjust PT to HKD23.0 (prior HKD22.0) factoring in the latest business trends post better- than- expected results. Risks include: (1) macro headwinds that lead to slowdown in consumption demand; (2) intensified competition in the local delivery and retail markets; (3) aggressive spending on new initiatives; and (4) achieving profitability takes longer than expected.

Hangzhou SF Intra- city Industrial Co., Ltd. is the largest third- party on- demand delivery service platform in China, providing customers with high- quality, high- efficiency, and multi- scenario third- party on- demand delivery services.

We have a Buy rating and PT of HKD23, based on a \(40\%\) discount to our targeted 2025E price to sales for its peer Dada, taking into account the traffic and user base of JD.com. Risks include (1) macro headwinds that lead to slowdown in consumption demand; (2) intensified competition in the local delivery and retail market; (3) aggressive spending on new initiatives; and (4) achieving profitability taking longer than expected.

We have a Buy rating and PT of USD2.20 based on P/E valuation, which is based on 8x 2024 EPADS at USD0.36. Risks include: (1) intensified competition in local delivery and retail markets; (2) aggressive spending on marketing to gain market share; and (3) achieving profitability takes longer than expected.

We have a Buy rating and PT of US \(60 / HK\) 233 based on 9.2x 2025E P/E (ex- new business). Key risks include (1) macro headwinds affecting GMV growth, especially in the electronics category; (2) intensified competition leading to margin pressure from aggressive marketing spending in the grocery category; and (3) user base growth in lower- tier cities falling below expectations on poor execution.

Buy - Describes securities that we expect to provide a total return (price appreciation plus yield) of \(15\%\) or more within a 12- month period. Hold - Describes securities that we expect to provide a total return (price appreciation plus yield) of plus \(15\%\) or minus \(10\%\) within a 12- month period. Underperform - Describes securities that we expect to provide a total return (price appreciation plus yield) of minus \(10\%\) or less within a 12- month period.

The expected total return (price appreciation plus yield) for Buy rated securities with an average security price consistently below \(10 is 20\%\) or more within a 12- month period as these companies are typically more volatile than the overall stock market. For Hold rated securities with an average security price consistently below \(10, the expected total return (price appreciation plus yield) is plus or minus 20% within a 12- month period. For Underperform rated securities with an average security price consistently below\) 10, the expected total return (price appreciation plus yield) is minus 20% or less within a 12- month period.

Jefferies Franchise Picks include stock selections from among the best stock ideas from our equity analysts over a 12 month period. Stock selection is based on fundamental analysis and may take into account other factors such as analyst conviction, differentiated analysis, a favorable risk/reward ratio and investment themes that Jefferies analysts are recommending. Jefferies Franchise Picks will include only Buy rated stocks and the number can vary depending on analyst recommendations for inclusion. Stocks will be added as new opportunities arise and removed when the reason for inclusion changes, the stock has met its desired return, if it is no longer rated Buy and/or if it triggers a stop loss. Stocks having 120 day volatility in the bottom quartile of S&P stocks will continue to have a 15% stop loss, and the remainder will have a 20% stop. Franchise Picks are not intended to represent a recommended portfolio of stocks and is not sector based, but we may note where we believe a Pick falls within an investment style such as growth or value.
